criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Stage 2.5-3 according to the Hoehn and Yahr scale (H&Y);

          -  Stable pharmacological treatment for the last 6 weeks before the enrolment and during
             the hospitalization;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any focal brain lesion detected in brain imaging studies (CT or MRI) performed in the
             previous 12 months;

          -  Drug-induced dyskinesias;

          -  Disturbing resting and/or action tremor, corresponding to scores 2-4 in the specific
             items of UPDRS III;

          -  Behavioral disturbances (evaluated with Neuropsychiatric Inventory);

          -  Visual and auditory dysfunctions according to the general clinical evaluation and
             medical history;

          -  cognitive decline (MMSE correct score < 24)
